advertising than non-advertising mail in the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Postal Service</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">mailstream</ENAMEX> will continue for <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the years</TIMEX> to come. This may have
serious political implications for the legal protection of the
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Postal Service</ENAMEX> monopoly on letter mail. The <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">public</ENAMEX> and the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Congress</ENAMEX>
may question such protection when they learn that the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Postal</ENAMEX>
Service is increasingly becoming an advertising medium.



<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">ANALYSIS</ENAMEX>



Introduction
The focus of this <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">paper</ENAMEX> is <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">First-Class Mail</ENAMEX>. First, we identify
